# Vercel — Production environment variables
# Import manually: Vercel Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Production
# Add each KEY below with your production Strapi URL (HTTPS, no trailing slash).

NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL=https://your-strapi.example.com

# Optional: max wait per Strapi request (ms). Keeps `next build` under Vercel limits when CMS is down.
# STRAPI_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS=10000

# ISR: TTL for Strapi `fetch()` Data Cache (seconds). On-demand updates via POST /api/revalidate.
# Route `export const revalidate` in App Router pages is a numeric literal (3600) — Next.js 16 cannot
# read this env in segment config; keep both aligned manually if you change the window.
# STRAPI_ISR_REVALIDATE_SECONDS=3600

# Shared secret for POST https://<your-domain>/api/revalidate (Strapi webhook: Authorization: Bearer …)
# REVALIDATE_SECRET=

# Logging (@driversclub/logger / tslog). Production defaults to JSON; override if needed.
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# LOG_FORMAT=json
# LOG_HIDE_POSITION=1

# Notes:
# - Must match the public URL of your Strapi instance (same host as media URLs).
# - `next/image` allows this host via `next.config.ts` remotePatterns + `/uploads/**`.
# - Strapi Cloud often uses `https://<id>.strapiapp.com` (wildcard is allowed in config).
# - In Strapi Admin → Settings → Users & Permissions → Public: enable `find` (and `findOne` where
#   applicable) for Homepage, Event, and Gallery so the Next.js server can read published content.
# - Strapi Admin → Settings → Webhooks: URL = `https://<your-domain>/api/revalidate`, Events = entry.* and
#   media.* as needed; Header `Authorization: Bearer <same as REVALIDATE_SECRET>`.
